Whoa, you got some mad skills! I heard about Pit Row's stolen cars. That ain't right, yo. You guys need payback.

S'been a while since anyone stepped up as a rival. Let's throw down some, then we'll see what we can do about those stolen rides.
I was holding out on you last time, but I ain't frontin' no more. From here on out, it ain't gonna be easy...
I heard about one of your missin' rides, so I'll make you a deal. Beat me one last time and I'll tell you what I know.
You caught me by surprise there, but anyone can get lucky once. I'm about to redefine the term pimp my ride.
Respect. I'll get my crew to keep an eye out for your stolen cars. You deserve it.

ASHLEIGH WINTHROP
OMG, our first VIP is DOA. I hope you know our highest class of racers are still waiting though.
You may have won, but you'll never be as fast as I am rich. At least I can buy a better car.
Summer's taken the loss real bad. I haven't seen her hit the mall this hard since Bryce posted a picture of her without make-up on Instawham.
Bryce is useless. A Gold Rusher should never lose, least of all to wannabes like you.
OMG. Like, why are you still here? Are you obsessed with me or something? Let's get this over with so I can go shopping.
I've heard you claim that I'm racing in a stolen car from Pit Row. Gross! I'd never drive a car from that place!
I'm totally a good person. Tell you what, if you beat me again, which you obviously won't, I'll tell you where I got this car.
Who do you think you are beating ME? Not to brag or anything, but I'm kind of a big deal. Most people just let me win.
Come to think of it, this car is a loser just like you. Hmmm... maybe it is from Pit Row.
You're a stronger racer than we thought, and that is one hell of a car. Where did you steal it?
You don't give up, do you? Sorry to hear your cars got stolen, but you're looking in the wrong place.
I remember now. We sold a sports car to a rich girl with a big mouth. Who cares if we stole it? We don't give refunds.
I can't quite believe this, but the Captain has requested to speak with you personally. Show some respect, grunt.
I've had my eye on Pit Row Racing for a while. Turned out they had some pretty nice cars... so I stole them.
I've heard the police are looking for us. You wouldn't happen to know anything about that, would you?
Building yourself an impressive car collection, I see. I'll have to get my crew to keep an eye on you.
You race well, but I don't have your cars anymore. I... misplaced them.
Thanks to you, the cops arrested half my crew. They won't get their hands on me and you can forget ever seeing your cars again.
I don't think I could've lost to a better driver. You got some crazy racers comin' up. Show 'em who's boss, yo!
OMG. You beat me again? Well, it doesn't matter how much you win. You'll always be my favorite loser. Good luck!
Well, you really are something, but you won't beat my boss, Daniel. He's gonna win the whole thing.
So the rumors about you are true. I heard you were fast, but I didn't think you were THAT fast.
Ladies and gentlemen, welcome to the final! Introducing the fastest racer in town - he's yet to lose a race - it's Victor Kidd!
That Grand Finals trophy will look perfect on my mantelpiece. I've cleared a space especially for it.
The engineers at Shax Industries have upgraded this car to be completely unbeatable. No more messing around.
You're a little faster than I expected. A couple of upgrades should take care of you.
Did you win? Sorry, I got distracted and didn't notice.
That's impossible! Mr. Shax, sir... I'm sorry.
Impressive. Most impressive. You're one step closer to that sponsorship deal, champ.
Good work, but I'm starting to spot some weaknesses. I'm sure we could work with those.
Completely unacceptable, John. You've let your personal life affect the business. You're fired. Go home and be a family man.
Victor! That was your second strike... and the third is your arrogance. Leave your car with security. You're fired.
I won't allow my authority to be undermined. Race me and the world will see your true colors - a lucky young punk who's out of their depth.
Pit Row Racing has been a thorn in my side since the day they set up shop. Who do you think gave Kurtz the order to steal their collection?
I remember. I had those cars scrapped for parts then sold them back to Pit Row. You've been buying Jerry's cars back all along... as upgrades.
I expected to lose. I am racing in a Pit Row car after all. It was by far the nicest in Jerry's collection, so I kept it for myself.
You want to know what happened to Jerry's cars? I do believe I gave one of them to Kurtz as payment. As for the rest... I can't quite remember.
Look at you all. Such arrogance. Such stupidity. You have no idea what I've been protecting this city from.

NITROUS
Upgrades increase your car's Performance Potential or PP.
Enter the daily races for big prizes.
Power is nothing without grip. Tire upgrades provide grip.
For the best starts, keep the needle in the green zone.
The shift indicator assumes full traction, so it's not perfect. Experiment to improve your times.
Wheelspin kills speed. Avoid it wherever you can!
There are multiple techniques to feather your gas for the perfect start. Experiment.
Different cars have different shift points.
The optimal time to activate your nitrous depends on many factors. You should consider your tire quality, tuning settings, number of upgrades fitted and more!
Follow CSR Racing 2 on Facebook: facebook.com/csrracinggame
Follow CSR Racing 2 on Twitter: @csrracing
No two cars are the same. Adapt to your ride.
Be strategic with your upgrade choices. Think ahead.
You can take higher-tier cars into lower-tier Regulation Races.
Winning a boss car is the ultimate sign that you're a serious driver!
You can change your license plate in the customize menu.
Stage 4 and 5 parts are import items that take time to be delivered.
Buying an item with gold skips the delivery times.
Different races use different amounts of fuel.
You can remove and refit parts that you have bought in the upgrade menu.
If you're finding a race difficult, fit some upgrades to increase your car's PP before trying it again.
Leveling up earns you free gold.
Purchasing cars or parts and winning events earns you RP.
Nitrous can be used in every race, experiment around the optimum time to use it.
If you've purchased Nitrous don't forget to use it!
Amateur and Pro Regulation Races are unlocked by winning Crew Battles.
Winning a Boss car gives you a great car to use in the next Tier!
Nitrous tuning allows you to alter the power and duration of your boost.
Tune your tire pressure to balance your car's acceleration against amount of wheelspin.
Unlock a new Garage space by increasing your car collection.
The more Daily Battles you win, the better the prizes!
Tuning your Final Drive allows you to customize your car's acceleration and top speed.
Don't forget to consider your tuning setup for half mile races.
Use Nitrous when light stops flashing

It all happened about 2 years ago.
Local warehouses had been [00FF00]violently broken[-] into and the police hadn't caught anyone yet.
It had been a tiring day, [00FF00]Donna[-] had delivered cars and [00FF00]Jess[-] stayed home as she was sick.
I decided to play the [00FF00]arcade[-] to blow off some steam and I lost track of time.
It started raining heavily outside and I could hear thunder in the distance.
The rain pounding on the roof and windows made a deafening sound.
In a roaring [00FF00]flash[-] the power went out!
Through the racket caused by the rain I could hear a [00FF00]faint rattling[-] sound...
The rattling grew [00FF00]louder[-] and suddenly stopped when something [00FF00]thumped[-] twice on the garage door.
Startled, I felt around in the [00FF00]darkness[-] of the garage, grabbed a torch and cautiously started investigating.
I flinched when I saw the car shadows dancing all around the garage...
Before realizing it was caused by my hand shaking unconsciously.
My hearing may not have been as sharp as in my younger days, but I could still hear the rattling through the rain.
Holding my torch I peered through the cold glass of the weather-battered window...
For a split second I caught a glimpse of a [00FF00]dreadfully pallid figure[-] headed towards the back of the building.
Whoever or whatever was [00FF00]lurking[-] was trying to get in.
I thought of getting in a car and driving the heck away, but with the [00FF00]power out[-] I couldn't open the garage door.
Are you still listening, kid?
The [00FF00]rattling sound[-] was now coming from the [00FF00]old emergency exit door[-] in the back.
It only took a few shakes for the rusty door to give way.
I didn't know what to do and my legs were failing.
I was [00FF00]trapped[-] like an old rat on a burning ship.
The door [00FF00]opened[-] with an [00FF00]atrocious[-] screech...
My heart jumped in my chest as I was [00FF00]face[-] to [00FF00]face[-] with...
[00FF00]Donna[-].
She had left her phone at Pit Row when delivering some cars earlier and really needed to make some calls.
The rattling came from the astounding amount of [00FF00]keys[-] she carries around with her...
Story time's over - have a [00FF00]Happy Halloween[-], kid!

Not bad! I've got an offer for someone with your talent. Come see me in the North-East part of town.
Welcome to Legends, friend. Beat these races and I'll hook you up with your first restoration project.
Nice driving. Looks like Jess was right about you after all...
I was hoping for a lot more than that... Looks like I need to look elsewhere.
Come on now, you're wasting time that I just don't have.
My sister left town years ago. She was into some heavy stuff with some bad people. You said she's back?
I don't have to worry about you leaving town as well... Do I?
You know, you can always walk away from this?
Is showing her up really worth it?
Alright, one to go. Win this and I'll let you own a little piece of history, the legendary Ferrari 250 GTO.
Great driving, friend. A promise is a promise so how about we get that Ferrari back to The Studio?
I don't just give cars to anyone, you gotta earn this!
Well, maybe I'll ask the Nu Fangz crew, they seem ready to make a few bucks.
Collect more Components and I'll make sure we restore your Ferrari so it's looking Pristine again.
Win this race, and we'll have enough Components to start restoring that rusty paint job.
I gotta say, that Ferrari suits you. Head back to The Studio - there's work to do!
Can't even win an easy race with this car, what are we going to do with you?
Keep at it, friend. My team needs more Components before we can restore your Ferrari and get you access to tuning.
I knew you wouldn't let me down. Remember, if you wanna tune that car it needs to be fully-restored.
Restoration is a long hard process. If you can't win here, you may as well quit while you're behind.
Slackers are bad for business. You're done.
Have you noticed the McLaren F1 parked up in The Studio? It's arguably the most iconic sports car in history and it can be yours...
Let's head back to The Studio and I'll tell you how.
You wanna know how to get hold of that McLaren or not?!
Components? I see. So using these, you're able to restore these cars and then access tuning. That's pretty neat.
Get a move on with that restoration, will you? I wanna work my tuning magic!
If you're struggling, there are always fusion parts to boost your performance. Go see Donna at Rare Imports.
I'm wondering just what the potential of these Legends cars is...
Mind if I take a look under your hood later? Maybe I'll get a better idea.
There's a limited number of car spaces free in The Studio. Win this and I'll tell you how to work on multiple Legends cars at once.
Once fully restored, Legends cars move into your main garage ready for tuning. That also makes room for new rides.
Winning this race would be a good start if you wanna restore more Legends cars.
I can tell you've been working closely with Jerry...
Do we need to go back to basics with KJ's crew?
That car is starting to take shape... I'm a little jealous, kid.
Maybe I should look into this car restoration? Izzy could be onto something big here.
Donna's got more fusion parts in stock if you feel your car needs a little performance boost.
No matter how a car looks, it's all about what's under the hood.
This is it, friend. Win this race and your whole world will change... You ready for the next chapter?
I can tell you're proud, but don't get too comfortable. Your next challenge involves Relay racing!
Losing does not promote these cars! Our restoration only sings when you win, got it?
Do I even have to say anything?
You've started your journey of car restoration, now I need you to go out and represent Legends.
There are Relay races about to go down. Show everyone why they need these cars and Components!
Orders are coming in fast after that race! Make sure you put on a show.
We need to be seen beating the competition. That means winning!
Try upgrading the car if you are having trouble with this one.
You're going to need two cars in the next race. Make sure you have another one ready.
This is a Relay race. It will require you to race both cars back to back. Don't let me down.
Now races will flip between your two cars, with a few Relays appearing. Let's do this!
I guess it was too soon to think you could handle a race like this.
Why don't you try and upgrade this car, you clearly need the boost?
You've started another car. I wonder just how far you can take this one?
Is there any car you can't drive?! Looking good, champ.
Jerry always said that if you're ever in trouble, grab parts at Donna's Rare Imports lot.
Don't worry, you'll get the next one.
Feeling the pressure yet? I was the same in my first Relay race, back when The TEMPE5T weren't such a big deal.
Don't worry about that TEMPE5T stuff I mentioned before, you just focus on racing.
The TEMPE5T would eat you up racing like this.
There was one guy, their leader... He was a scary dude.
Sometimes you know... I like to think I could have run The TEMPE5T.
I thought about joining one of the street crews once, but Jerry was always on my case. I wonder why?
The TEMPE5T? Yeah I've heard things. You're best off just focusing on restoration.
I can take a look under the hood if you want? Might be a problem.
You are losing pretty bad, maybe you should talk to Jerry.
My sister always picks the hardest events.
How's Jess doing? Are you looking out for her?
Don't rely too much on Jerry. You need people who are going to push you.
I don't want to have to throw you to the wolves.
I'd do this myself but I need to keep a low profile.
Hey, kid. If you're starting to have a bit of trouble get that car back to Pit Row for some tuning.
Always remember to retune your car if you're having trouble with a race.
Whatever the outcome, kid, Jess and I have always got your back.
When you're ready, I have a dealer back in Japan that can get you access to some high-end cars.
Great driving. You decided what your next Legends investment is gonna be?
Upgrade, tune, fuse the car! Whatever it takes to win!
Do you really think that she'll let you have her F1? She loves that car. It's a part of this city's racing history.
I kept it safe down in The Studio. It was the only thing I had to remember her by...
You have to win! I... Don't want her to leave again...
You can do this, just have to look under the hood.
Get this done, friend, and we'll ramp it up. I've got big plans for you!
I should've found you sooner. Once you're done giving yourself a pat on the back, come find me.
Maybe I should've have asked Donna, I heard she can race?
I'm not someone you want to disappoint...
And you thought you were ready to take my car for a spin?!
In these races I'm going to need another Legends car added to the mix. What have you got?
Don't forget that, just cos I call you friend, this is primarily a business arrangement.
However, keep this up, and I don't know how I couldn't be your friend!
Get into The Studio and upgrade that car... Now!
Lose again and I'll strip that new car for parts. Whether you are sat in it or not!
I knew someone who used to own a ride just like yours. It was a real beauty!
Izzy's really putting you through it... Why won't she answer my calls?
Don't worry, let's re-plan and get back to it.
Wonder where Izzy is hiding now?
I feel like I owe you an explanantion as to why I'm back. I'm ready to talk.
I thought long and hard about showing up here again. I know I hurt Jess.
This is why you don't make friends... They let you down.
Don't come back till you've won this race.
Frustrating... Let's look under the hood.
I was pretty young the night Izzy left. I didn't understand anything at the time.
For years I thought it was my fault, but then I learned the truth. Well, rumours of the truth.
If you keep losing, maybe try and get hold of some fusion parts?
Nice race, you were close!
Those perfect shifts will really make the difference in a close race.
The night I abandoned Jess was the single worst day of my life.
I bet everything that night and lost. Leaving town was the only way I could guarantee my sister's safety.
You think I'm hard on you! But I'm getting you ready for someone worse.
One day he'll come down here looking for me. We need to be ready.
He doesn't go easy on anyone.
The night Izzy left, she told me what happened. I was devastated I wasn't there for her.
I swore to Izzy that I wouldn't let Jess fall into the same trouble.
Izzy might well stretch the truth, so don't trust all of her stories.
I know I'm hard on her, but she broke Jess's heart.
We still don't know why she's really back in town.
I was rolling with crews like Shax and The TEMPE5T alike. Using their money to win races and double it. I was unstoppable.
The night I left I bet bigger than ever before with The TEMPE5T's money... And I lost.
If you gamble, you better know what you're in for!
Don't waste MY time or MY money...
I don't get why Izzy was taking those kind of risks. What's the point?!
I can't help but think the worst... Why did she want so much cash? What was she planning?!
Have you spoken to her? Why would she do that?!
When we were kids, she told me we'd have our own restoration shop. I believed her.
I've been running from The TEMPE5T for years. All over the world - UK, Japan, even remote parts of Europe.
I'm done running. I need to fight back.
You'd not last in Japan racing like that. You'd be just another drifter.
We are so close. Don't let me down now!
I heard rumours for years. It's hard to know what's true and what's a bunch of lies.
I know you're busy, but if you can help her... Please do.
I can tell you're getting distracted by my drama. How about I shut up and you focus?
Maybe your car needs a tune-up.
I had to grab what I could. Before I left I made Jerry swear to look after Jess for me.
Jess is the only family I have. I can't explain the lengths I'd go to for her!
I'm closer than ever to making up for lost time.
We can't let Jess down now! I mean me... You can't let ME down now!
I know Izzy's got her side of the story, but I still have my doubts. Can I trust her?
You're right. If she wasn't trustworthy, why would she even be back here?
I'll take a look under the hood.
I've contacted Donna, she's expecting you, and your bronze keys.
Legends can give us the cars we can use to take down The TEMPE5T once and for all.
There's no doubt about it, we're coming back strong! Just maybe Jess can have a better life.
You've gotta do a lot better than that to stand up to The TEMPE5T.
I won't be forced out of town again!
Everyone can see how beautiful these Legends are, now let's show them how quick they can be too.
Don't start believing your hype, friend. We've got a way to go yet.
I'm not going to lose my temper.
You know the drill! Get working on that car's upgrades.
These races are purely about your finishing speed. Make sure you smile for the camera!
More of these Legends cars? I've been hearing about them from everyone! They're the new buzz!
You're rewriting history in this city. I'm so excited! What does this mean for all of us?
What's the secret of improving the performance? Has Izzy told you anything?
You were close, Champ. Don't give up.
The key to successful business is product placement. Now place this car at the finish line... In 1st!
Yes, friend! The road we are paving before us is pure gold.
Another key to business is a leading product! That means you win.
What part of 'win this race' is a problem for you?
Last place is not good for business!
If you aren't driving a Legends car, you ain't a real racer! That's the word going round, anyway.
You really can do anything, can't you?
I've got your back! Let's get some cash together and upgrade.
Izzy can be a scary lady... Don't cross her.
I wonder what would happen if we were one happy family again.
Legends will be our legacy in this city... Where we go from here is up to you.
That racer didn't even see you coming! Our orders are through the roof!
Well, well, well. Here we are again...
How are you meant to get those cars for Jerry if you race like this?!
All I'm hearing about is Components, Legends and Izzy. It's crazy. What have you started, kid?
Whatever it is, don't stop! We've never had so much business.
Don't forget that Donna might have some Stage 6 parts you can use.
If you haven't maxed the fusion on the car, I recommend you do so.
Imagine... If you could add even more fusion to this baby.
Components are a clever little thing I devised. You can't fake them or cheat me. I can't work on cars till you get them.
There were a lot of cheats back in the day, now these little things are like gold dust!
You know you can just give me the Components if you don't use them?
Hmmm...
Hey! I heard Izzy is back in town. Is that true?
We dated a long time ago. She... She broke my heart man.
You'd tell me if she was, right?
She can't be, no way she'd mess with a slow racer like you!
Date KJ? Do I look like someone who was ever that desperate?
I love money and power. No man can replace that! Especially a chump like KJ!
Maybe I should speak with KJ. He might be a better prospect than you!
I'm going to pretend you never said that, so that you can focus on racing!
I left Izzy a voicemail, told her this is the last time I'm calling...
Izzy called back! She wants to meet. I've never been so nervous! Wish me luck.
We were better off when it was just you, me and Jerry.
And Donna of course. She has our backs.
I feel I can trust you. Components aren't the only trick up my sleeve...
I think you're ready for the big one. Come with me... You're closer than ever to owning that McLaren F1.
I really thought you were the one for this next job...
They will be here soon, I know it.
We've been in one spot for too long!
This is what Legends is all about. Win this and we go down in Los Derivas history.
The most epic comeback since Jerry's famous summer of 1962!
All I ask is that one of the cars is a Legends Lamborghini. Other than that, the remaining 4 cars are your choice.
Your cars are set, so go take these losers to the cleaners!
Childs play. I'm getting the winnings, keep going.
Pop the hood, let's have a look at the issue.
Izzy told me her vision. Sounds crazy. I hope that The TEMPE5T don't come for her.
You're right. With you here, no-one is coming for her again.
Shax will challenge her to race. You need a fast collection!
Get some fusion parts, maybe even Stage 6?
You've got quite the collection now... Let's show them what we're about!
Another win and our reputation continues to grow! Shall we?
You shouldn't be struggling at this point.
Donna always has parts we could use, right?
Legends... A brand that covers the globe. That's Izzy's vision.
I think Izzy will do it, and we'll support you both where we can.
No worries, we'll take the car back into the shop and work on it.
These races are tough...
But you've got this!
You hear the talk on the streets right? I do.
It sounds like... Freedom!
You clearly don't hear it.
Hmm...
Jess told me everything. We're here for you kid.
Legends will change the world, let's ensure that happens.
Donna has some more parts. Give her Lot a call.
Don't worry kid. Sometimes you win some, and some you lose.
I'll take a look under the hood.
When I was in Japan, I learned a few customization techniques...
Maybe one day I'll show you, see what you make of it.
In Japan, you don't look your employer in the eye if you let them down like that!
I guess Legends doesn't mean as much to you as it does to me?
I see Izzy is still ice cold...
I've got to give it to her, she really knows how to shake up the town.
I still can't believe you beat me by the way.
Shift, control... I'm just trying to figure out what's going through your head.
We've built Legends into something people can believe in...
Now let's show the haters why they shouldn't have ever thought any different.
Well, well, look who lost again!
I've told you before, friend; Legends cars don't lose!
Get back out there!
You are killing it! Let's go all the way!
I thought I saw a shady guy over there. Who was that?
Remember to nail those perfect shifts!
Sometimes a perfect shift isn't the best way to race certain cars.
These rides are really something. You've done a great job, friend.
It's getting close to really showing this city what we've got.
Don't worry about what Jess saw!
Focus on your races!
We can't lose now!
What have we here?!
Well, well... We knew that thief Izzy would show up back here eventually.
Get out of my face!
You know someone called Izzy?
My people are starting to make preparations. Soon we'll start increasing the rarity of these beauties.
With my techniques, no racer alive will be able to beat you ever again!
I'll tell my people to head back home.
You aren't ready for what they have to offer.
Soon there will be nothing in our way to trigger what I like to call... Legends: Phase 2.
We own Los Derivas now... Next stop... Who knows.
You aren't ready for Phase 2.
What was I thinking?
This life... It's not for you.
Legends has become so big. I think it's time to mop up the rest of the city.
The TEMPE5T won't know what's hit them with these rides!
Maybe I spoke too soon...
Check out Rare Imports for some extra fusion parts.
Can't believe we've made it to this point. Win this, and the final challenge is on!
So what do you say? Is there one more challenge left in you?
You really looked out for Izzy. I can't thank you enough.
You did good, kid! This family might be on the mend.
This is the biggest moment of your life...
Don't blow it here. Stay focused!
Don't let us down here!
No way! You really got Izzy's F1? I wasn't sure if that was just a fake promise.
No one will be able to touch you with a car like that. Can I tune it?! I'm freaking out!
What do you say, one last run to really elevate your game? The McLaren F1 tests even the most gifted racers.
Fully-upgrade this car, and I'm telling you, it's one of the quickest in the world.
No-one's ever ready at this point.
I expected more from you, friend.
Focus everything into that F1. You're gonna need it if The TEMPE5T come back.
I'm starting to regret giving you that car... I hate losing!
You just don't give up, do you?
Good... But not good enough.
Just when you thought life couldn't get any better, huh?
Keep your eyes on the road, friend. Wouldn't want you getting hurt now, would we?
Um... No. Try again.
Maybe you aren't ready for this legacy just yet...
I could give you the parts now... Nah, you have to earn this.
This is going to be fun.
Alright, I'll give you some credit where its due. That was a good race.
I was made for this life.
Don't sulk! In life there are no freebies, don't expect different here!
Turn your car around, and try again!
Don't relax, there are people out there who will tempt you into a life you aren't ready for.
Stand up to The TEMPE5T, no matter what. Understand?
Like it or not, you and your friends are part of it now. You need to get better.
Am I speaking another language? Or are you just hard of hearing? Which is it?
What has Jerry been teaching you this whole time?!
There's thousands of racers in this city... Let's show them who really runs these streets.
The streets are alive with the talk of that race.

Hey, you. I need you to help me stop Hobbs.
Last time I saw you, I told you to dispose of those computer chips.
Did you? Nah, 'course you didn't.
Know how I know that? Because I just got word that Hobbs is trying to trade them to clear your names.
Now, let's catch him, before he does something stupid.
Shaw's back? Oh, great.
Look, Hobbs has gone  out to try to get those chips to the right people.
Said he's selling them to some guy called... Brixton?
Letty wouldn't talk to me.
What did she say to you?
Brixton? Oh, that's not good. That's really not good at all.
Wait, why are we with this guy again?
Because your bicep-brained friend is selling computer chips to the most dangerous man in the world.
Naturally, we have to stop him, because otherwise he's going to do a lot of damage.
Alright, alright, no need to go all MI6 on me. I'm not gonna leave them on a train, chill.
Alright, gather some info. We've got to know where he's going.
Okay, that guy said a burly guy matching the description blitzed through here a couple days ago.
Said he asked some questions rather forcefully.
Consdering Hobbs has all the subtlety of a tranqulised rhino, I'm guessing that was him.
Let's keep moving.
Hobbs can't be far away now, I can practically smell the protein powder.
Alright, word is that he's on the other side of the city.
I'll see you there.
Brixton is dangerous. I've worked with him before.
He shouldn't be on the scene any more, because... well, never mind.
I'm worried Hobbs might be walking into a trap.
Worse yet, I think that he thinks he's got the upper hand on Brixton - he doesn't.
How do we know Shaw isn't working with Brixton?
For all we know, there could be a secret cabal of Angry British Guys.
Rumor is that Brixton has been augmenting himself with some top-secret stuff.
I guess we'll have to see what he's like in person. Let's hope Hobbs doesn't try and start a fistfight with him.
Who am I kidding...
Brixton was on our list for a long time.
He even used to be part of MI6 - Blacklist stuff.
I thought he was dead...
Alright - he's near.
Let's try to intercept this deal before it goes bad.
There he is, and there's Brixton - see if you can get his attention!
Hobbs! Don't give him the chips!
Oh, great. The bad guy has the computer chips. Fantastic.
Right. Let's see what Brixton is up to. You need to go undercover.
Look, this Brixton guy is bad news. And he knows all of us.
But he doesn't know you - he didn't see you in the commotion. Try to get in there, win his trust.
I got word they were after Letty - I had to give the chips over. Didn't seem like such a bad idea at the time.
Alright, you've been trouncing his crew. I think you've got his attention.
Nice.
Look, Brixton is a bit unhinged. I think he thinks of himself as a necessary evil.
I need you to go climb his ranks.
Word out there is that Brixton is building an army... what is he up to?
Alright, Rook, turns out I made a mistake giving those chips to Brixton.
How was I to know he was a psychopathic Bad Guy?
You literally could have just asked, you t-
Guys, please. We're going to need to work together here. Save the testosterone for another time.
Looks like Brixton has let you in.
Don't betray his trust - yet.
See if you can find out what he's after. It might give us a clue or two to his plans.
Okay, we've intercepted his communications thanks to his work.
Here's some instructions he sent to one of his lieutenants:
'The person I need to find is dangerous, and has been undercover for years.'
'But I know exactly where she'll be.'
Ah. He's sent through a name. This is... not good.
He needs an active MI6 agent to properly activate those chips.
And he's going after my sister.
Alright, I don't like Shaw, but I know how important family is. Find Hattie.
He's after Hattie? That complete and utter b- I need a second. Get to her before he does. Or before she gets to him.
Hey, you. Got time for a few rides?
Beat me here, and I'll let you in on a secret...
Wait, you're trying to catch Brixton as well? Good, now I don't have to waste you.
And Deck's here? ...You're going to have to explain.
Any more news? Thank you for letting my brother know I was here, by the way.
Yes, that was sarcastic. He can be distractingly direct sometimes. He thinks he's a paragon of stealth, and he's just not.
Once the siblings have stopped squabbling, make sure you don't let them get their hands on those chips.
We need to destroy them once and for all - save the world, and all that.
Alright, Brixton's plan is in motion.
He says his heist is taking place downtown.
Oh, he's trying to keep us away from downtown?
Well, I know exactly where I'm going to be in two weeks.
And me.
No. I've been tracking this guy for years, and he needs to come in properly and quietly. I do this, with the Rookie.
Stop, Brixton! You don't know what you're doing!
Great. Now he's played you both, and he's got Hattie.
That's it - we're going after him. Where's he going... West Coast?
At least it's not Siberia again...
I can see why he's after her.
He probably needs an active MI6 agent to activate those chips.
We probably should have seen that coming. What does he need the chips for?
You know, all of this wouldn't have happened if you'd just destroyed the chips like I asked.
Apparently your sister is nearby.
Great. And if you'd let me handle this, she wouldn't have been captured.
At least you're driving. Last time I drove with Hobbs, he crashed like four cars.
Five, actually.
...You're actually proud of that, aren't you?
Hattie's tough. She'll be okay.
Unlike her brother, then.
They're nearby, I can smell it.
Are you sure that's not just, you know, you...?
Let's get Hattie, before he does the Bad Guy Speech.
Flank him! The chips are activated, you've got to destroy them!
Nice escape - but we've got to free Hattie. Hobbs is fending him off.
Follow that car! Hattie is in there!
If you can get in front of this car, we can get Hattie back.
Late as usual, brother... but thank you.
...Where's Hobbs?
Oh, damn it. Now we've got to go back him up, don't we.
Are we sure he hasn't just punched his way out?
Brixton has ghosted us.
His stealth skills are legendary. And I saw him take a couple punches from Hobbs with no issue.
Wow. That's impressive. Say what you want about Hobbs, but he can definitely lay a few hits on.
Only because he literally doesn't have the brains to think of anything else.
I think I see them in the distance.
Run, Rook - escape with those chips and destroy them! He gets weaker the further away they are from him!
Here, take this {0}! It belonged to a friend of a friend once. It's the fastest we got.

At this rate, we are going to break the sound barrier itself!
I believe in you. Lets try one more time and find out.

ANOTHER RECORD FOR US!!!
Dont give up now! You and that Gemera were destined to win!

How does it feel to be in the fastest car in Los Derivas? You did great out there!
Dont you dare give up now! You and that Gemera were destined to win!
249 Mph! I knew it could do it! Thank you for being on this journey with me.
Perhaps a small error. Lets try again!
Making fast cars is hard work but a lot of fun. I really enjoyed our time together.
Heres a little parting gift. Drive safe!
If we make this happen, Im giving you a {0} to celebrate!
Keep this up and the {0} is yours to keep!
And they said a hybrid couldnt compete. Ha! Thanks for showing them what it can do.
Youve got the worlds most powerful production car ever built. You can do this!
And just like that! The impossible becomes possible. We make a great team.
We are so close, I can feel it! Lets try again.
Hmmmm. I wonder what is holding us back. Lets get back to the garage and see what we can do.
You know? I think I have an idea that might help us. Lets get back to the garage and take a look.

Log in to collect your daily login bonus rewards.
Your daily bonus rewards get better as you continue to login on consecutive days.

Open bronze crates to get fusion parts.
Opening Bronze crates multiple times will unlock a loyalty reward.
Bronze crates will drop Stage 6 upgrades as the loyalty reward.

Open silver crates to get 1 - 5 star cars.
Silver crate drops the prestige cup car of the season as the loyalty reward, which can be unlocked by opening the crate multiple times.

Open gold crates to get 3-5 star cars.
Opening gold crates multiple times will unlock a loyalty reward.
Gold crates drop an extra car as the loyalty reward.

It sure is, Jess! Feast your eyes on the {0}!
It certainly is a beauty. Quite the punk take on the classic Porsche 911. Love it!

Well, youve come to the right place. That sounds like its going to be an absolute treat to watch. Lets get started then!
Woah! That sounded spectacular and the {0} sure flies!

Mid engine you say? Howd you manage to pull that off on a classic 911 silhouette?

Only one way to find out.
What a drive! I dont think Ive had this much fun in a while.
Im glad you enjoyed it. I think the {0} might just be ready to take on the Pikes.

Jess, do you know what sets the Aston Martin Vantage line apart?

Just a few years older than you! Haha

How does the Valour really capture the Legacy of the brand?
The only front-engine V12 sports car available with a manual transmission, its purist approach is unique in 2023 and a thrilling tribute to a golden era of driving.
The Valour's release marks a milestone. Its carbon fibre construction embodies strength, agility, and sustainabilityan embodiment of Aston Martin's commitment to craftsmanship and the environment
A blend of past and future. I think I'd call it a legacy in motion!
I can't wait to witness the Valour on the road.
Did you know Aston Martin has been crafting automotive dreams for 110 glorious years!
110 years! That's incredible! What do you think keeps them going?
Their drive for innovation, their passion and the elegance they deliver just blend so well! You can clearly see it in all their cars. It just shines through!
Ive always wondered about those wings on the logo.
The wings symbolise the brands relentless pursuit of speed and freedom, dating all the way back to the early days of racing!
Talking about the early days, do you have a favourite Aston Martin era?
I'd say the roaring 60s. The DB5 , the silver screen and the birth of a legend!

Aston Hill? I've heard the name, but tell me more about the connection it shares with Aston Martin.
Aston Hill, a sacred testing ground for Aston Martin since its inception, where racing legends like Sir Stirling Moss etched their mark, shaping a legacy defined by speed and precision.
Aston Hill holds all that history, but how does it talk about the future?
The hill signifies a journeya pilgrimage from the classics of yesteryear to the boundless innovation of tomorrow.
Speaking of the future, have you caught wind of the Aston Martin Valkyrie AMR Pro?
The Valkyrie AMR Pro, the hypercar designed to conquer the 24 Hours of Le Mans circuit in a mere 3 minutes and 20 seconds! Yes, it's truly an insane marvel!

A track-focused marvel, pushing the boundaries of aerodynamics and performance. The Valkyrie AMR Pro stands as a testament to Aston Martin's unwavering commitment to delivering unparalleled driving experiences.
How did Aston Martin sculpt such a masterpiece?

Aston Martin collaborated with the brilliance of Formula 1 maestro Adrian Newey and Red Bull Racing to craft the Valkyrie AMR Pro, seamlessly merging race technology with the inherent elegance of Aston Martin.
Aston Martin's journey is genuinely extraordinary.
From the hallowed grounds of Aston Hill to the cutting-edge Valkyrie AMR Pro, the brand continues its evolution.
It's a saga scripted with passion, innovation, and an unwavering commitment to pushing the boundaries of automotive excellence.
Here's to Aston Martin's rich history and the thrilling chapters that await!
